Place cranberries in a small bowl and cover with very hot water; set aside. Melt butter in a large heavy pot over high heat. Scrape in vanilla seeds; discard pod. Add brown sugar and salt and cook, stirring, until combined. Add apples and cook, stirring often, until apples are soft and liquid is almost completely evaporated, 15â€“20 minutes. Transfer apple mixture to a large serving bowl. Drain cranberries, add to apple mixture, and toss to combine.